sentences: López-Nussa gave a concert in the 2006 Montreux Jazz Festival and recorded with Claude Nobs support, "Sobre el Atelier" in a Swiss studio.
López-Nussa was born into a musical family in Havana on July 13, 1983.
He started on piano when he was eight years old, attending the Manuel Saumell Elementary School of Music and Amadeo Roldán Conservatory.
Two years later, he participated in a piano contest at the Montreux Jazz Festival and won first place.
He released his first solo album, Canciones, in 2007.
